You know that feeling when you're walking in the city with your family and you suddenly felt raindrops in the middle of the day but you don't see any clouds? You then tell them to prepare the umbrella but they won't listen because there is no sign of rain. You feel like you're insignificant and your words do not matter. You may think that in the eyes of God you are but one ant amongst billions in his garden and that it matters not when you drown whilst He waters His plants. You might be wrong. Because there are other ants who are not any different from you. They can make their own decisions and habe their own thoughts. And your assumptions about them aren't always right. Then there's me.
